### User Management API Check File
### Base URL: https://todu.mn/bs/lms/v1
### Supports: List users, Create user, Get user, Update user, Delete user
### Note: All endpoints require authentication (admin role for create/update/delete).

@baseUrl = https://todu.mn/bs/lms/v1
@userId = 12345

### 1. List all users
# GET /users
# Headers: Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
# Response: { "items": [ { id, username, first_name, last_name, email, phone, picture, ... } ] }
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 2. Create a new user (admin only)
# POST /users
# Headers: Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
# Request body: username, password, first_name, last_name, email, phone, facebook_id (optional)
# Note: Role assignment is done via school membership (see school.check.http)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "johndoe",
  "password": "secret123",
  "first_name": "John",
  "last_name": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "phone": "99119911",
  "facebook_id": ""
}

### 3. Get user by ID
# GET /users/{user_id}
# Headers: Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
# Response: { id, username, first_name, last_name, email, phone, picture, is_active, ... }
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 4. Update user (admin only)
# PUT /users/{user_id}
# Headers: Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
# Request body: fields to update (email, family_name, first_name, last_name, phone, picture)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Johnathan",
  "last_name": "Doe",
  "phone": "99229922",
  "email": "johnathan.doe@example.com"
}

### 5. Delete user (admin only)
# DELETE /users/{user_id}
# Headers: Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
# Request body may contain current_user (auto-filled)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 6. Get courses of a specific user (enrollments)
# GET /users/{user_id}/courses
# Headers: Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
# Response: { "items": [ { course_id, group_id, payment_amount, ... , "course": { name } } ] }
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}/courses
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 7. Get schools of a specific user
# GET /users/{user_id}/schools
# Headers: Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
# Response: { "items": [ { id, name, picture, priority, "role": { name } } ] }
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}/schools
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}